AN AWARDS ceremony is to highlight the achievements of Scotland's ethnic minorities. Awards will honour city's ethnic groups AN AWARDS ceremony is to highlight the achievements of Scotland's ethnic minorities.The Scottish Minority Ethnic Achievement Awards will be held at the Crowne Plaza on October 24.The annual awards offer a platform to showcase, highlight and reward organisations and individuals who have made an outstanding contribution in their respective fields.From dynamic young entrepreneurs to established veterans, minority ethnic businesses continue to make an impact on Scotland's economic success.Deputy First Minister Nicola Sturgeon MSP will be speaking at the event.Organisers are still looking for nominations across a variety of categories, including Business, Social Enterprise, Environment, Sport, Education, Employment, Housing and Philanthropy.The nominations close on Wednesday.For more information, visit www.cemvoscotland.org.uk 